Package net.sf.jclec.mo.indicator

Quality indicator package.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AdditiveEpsilon
    The additive epsilon indicator (I_e+) considers the amount by which a Pareto set should be translated in order to dominate the other Pareto set.
    BinaryIndicator
    Abstract binary indicator.
    Epsilon
    The Epsilon indicator (I_e) obtains the minimum 'epsilon' value, i.e.
    ErrorRatio
    The Error Ratio (ER) indicates the number of vectors in the Pareto front that are not members of the second Pareto front.
    GeneralizedSpread
    The Spread indicator measures the extent of the Pareto front approximation with respect to the second Pareto front.
    GenerationalDistance
    The Generational Distance (GD) measures how far the Pareto front is from the second (true) Pareto front.Objective values in the range [0,1] are recommended to compute distances.
    HyperareaRatio
    The Hyperarea Ratio (HR) computes the ratio between the hyperarea (hypervolume) of two Pareto fronts.
    Hypervolume
    The Hypervolume (HV) obtains the hyper-area covered by a given Pareto front.
    Indicator
    Abstract indicator for measure the quality of the Pareto front.
    InvertedGenerationalDistance
    The Inverted Generational Distance (IGD) measures how far the true Pareto front is from the Pareto front.
    MaximumError
    The Maximum Pareto Front Error (ME) describes how far are the two sets and how well they conform in shape.
    NVA
    The NonDominated Vector Addition (NVA) indicator measures the difference in the number of non dominated solutions between two fronts.
    ONVG
    The Overall Nondominated Vector Generation (ONVG) is defined as the total number of non dominated vector found during the search, i.e. the size of the Pareto front.
    ONVGR
    The Overall Nondominated Vector Generation Ratio (ONVGR) is defined as the ratio of the total number of non dominated vectors in the front to the number of vectors in the second front.
    R2
    The R2 indicator compares the quality of the Pareto front approximation and the second (true) Pareto front in terms of the proximity to a reference point.
    R3
    The R3 indicator compares the quality of the Pareto front approximation and the true Pareto front in terms of the proximity to a reference point.
    RelativeProgress
    The Progress indicator measures the relative convergence improvement in terms of generational distance.
    Spacing
    The Spacing (S) describes the spread of solutions in a given Pareto set.
    Spread
    The Spread indicator measures the extent of the Pareto front approximation with respect to the true Pareto front.
    TernaryIndicator
    Abstract ternary indicator.
    TwoSetCoverage
    The Two Set Coverage CS(A,B), defines the ratio of the number of solutions in front B that are dominated by solutions in front A to the number of solutions in B.
    UnaryIndicator
    Abstract unary indicator.
